body:
I have an Xamarin Forms application and I am trying to load and assign a font to a SKPaint.Typeface.  I can can successfully load the font file from embedded resources but after assigning the Typeface.....its still null.  I thought maybe the file was corrupt so I tried multiple different ttf files, but SelectedText.Typeface is always null.  I found a guy having a similar issue on stack overflow, followed the correct answer on there but still not working. 

**Code**
```
public static SKPaint SelectedText => new SKPaint { Color = SKColors.Black, FakeBoldText = true, Style = SKPaintStyle.Stroke, StrokeWidth = .6f };

private static SKTypeface GetFont()
{
    SKTypeface sKTypeface = null;
            
    using (var resource = Assembly.GetExecutingAssembly().GetManifestResourceStream("MyApp.Resource.Roboto-Regular.ttf"))
    {
         SKTypeface result = SKTypeface.FromStream(resource);
    }
    return sKTypeface;
}

// Typeface is always null after assigning GetFont() with the method above 
SelectedText.Typeface = GetFont();  


I have also tried both of these...and both return sans-serif no matter what font name i reference.  
var test = SKTypeface.FromFamilyName(SKFontManager.Default.GetFamilyName(1).ToString());
var test2 = SKFontManager.Default.MatchFamily("arial", SKFontStyle.Normal);

```
**Expected Behavior**
I would expect that SelectedText.Typeface would show the font information not null

**Actual Behavior**
SelectedText.Typeface shows null after assigning the font

<!-- a general description of what really happened -->

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  Im currently using Skiasharp.Views.Forms 2.80.0.  I tried upgrading but still had the same issue.  The upgraded version has an issue with SVG layout so I have been using an older version.  
- Last known good version:  Unknown
- IDE:  Windows Visual Studio 
- Platform Target Frameworks: <!-- all that apply, remove the platforms that aren't broken or haven't had any testing -->
- Android: 12, I have been using an actual device, Samsung Galaxy S10+, Model number SM-G975U1
